            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Hd1e108">Rubrica 15</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De fruitione pecunie</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>
      ¶ De fruitione pecunie. Rubrica. 15
      <lb ed="#V" n="70"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Rd1e113">SAlomon in ecclesiast. c.
      <lb ed="#V" n="71"/>5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Qd1e122">Omnis 
               ho<lb ed="#V" n="72" break="no"/>mini cui dedit deus diuitias atque
        <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>substantiam: potestatemque ei tribuit vt
        <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>comedat ex eis et fruatur parte sua et letetur
        <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>de labore suo: hoc est donum dei.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-d1e134">
               <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Rd1e134">Aristoteles retho. li. i. c. 7.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Qd1e138">Diuitem esse est in
        <lb ed="#V" n="77"/>vti. magisquam in possidere.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-d1e144">
               <lb ed="#V" n="78"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Rd1e146">Seneca de beata vita:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Qd1e148">Diuitie apud 
               sapi<lb ed="#V" n="79" break="no"/>entem virum in seruitute sunt: apud stultum in imperio.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-d1e155">
               <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Rd1e159">Auctor l. de for. hone. vite. c. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Qd1e159">Non que
        <lb ed="#V" n="81"/>apud te habes tanquam aliena seruabis: sed pro
        <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>te tanquam tua et dispones et vtaris.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-d1e167">
               <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Rd1e173">Cato. c. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Qd1e171">Fac sumptum propere cum res
        <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>desiderat ipsa.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-d1e177"> 
          / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Rd1e183">Capitulo. 5. et fi.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="85"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Qd1e179">Utere quesitis opibus: fuge nomen auari.
        <lb ed="#V" n="86"/>Quid tibi diuitie si pauper semper abundas. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-d1e187">
               <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Rd1e197">Uersificator fabularum esopi fab. 12.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="88"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Qd1e191">Tristior immensas pauperat vsus opes.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-d1e197">
               <lb ed="#V" n="89"/>
                / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Rd1e209">Fabula. 27</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="90"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Qd1e201">Pauperius nihil est quam miser vsus opum. <!--229.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="95-v"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
               </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-d1e213">
               <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Rd1e227">Auctor l. qui dicitur facetus. c. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d76006-Qd1e217">Sit bene
        <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>vestitus cui non fit par.
        <lb ed="#V" n="3"/>Et culte viuat potibus atque cibis.</quote>
            </p>
